# Data Cleaning

## Overview
Data cleaning is a critical first step in any data science or AI project. Clean data ensures accurate analysis and reliable model performance.

## Key Concepts
- Handling missing values (drop, fill, interpolate)
- Removing duplicates
- Fixing inconsistent formatting
- Detecting and handling outliers

## Techniques Used
- Pandas functions such as:
  - dropna()
  - fillna()
  - drop_duplicates()
- Data type conversion for consistency

## Why It Matters
Poor data quality leads to inaccurate models and unreliable insights. Clean data improves model performance and decision-making.

## Real-World Application
Used in preprocessing pipelines before training machine learning models to ensure reliable predictions.
